<TITLE> 3 killed in road accident in Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Jun 8 (bdnews24.com)  At least three people were killed in a head-on collision between two good-laden trucks at Kamarkhand Upazila in Sirajganj. Police said the accident occured Tuesday dawn on the Dhaka-Bogra highway near Kashem intersection in the upazila's Jhaoil area. One of the three dead was indentified as Shafiqul Islam, 35, a resident of Bogra. Riazuddin, police sub-inspector of Bangabandhu Bridge police station (west), said that at about 3am on Tuesday, a truck, carrying poultry feed, was immobilised when it was involved in a collision with a bus. When the truck was being repaired, another Dhaka-bound fish-carrying truck from Maymensingh rammed into the stranded truck . The driver, helper and a passenger in the fish-carrying truck died on the spot, the police offcial added. Later, the bodies were sent to the Sirajganj General Hospital morgue for autopsy, Riazuddin said. Traffic remained stalled on the road until 6 am. 
